## Context

- All 5 phases of PTEN atlas development pipeline complete (tasks 463-468 all done)
- Phase 1: 209 PTEN-lost lines classified, 9 qualifying cancer types
- Phase 2: PIK3CB positive control PASSES (Breast d=-2.23, Skin d=-1.50). AKT2 ROBUST in Lymphoid.
- Phase 3: 0 genome-wide significant hits (power-limited: 5-34 PTEN-lost lines per type, 18K FDR correction). PIK3CB Breast FDR=0.10 just misses threshold. Priority targets report generated.
- Phase 4: Afuresertib (AKT inhib) strong PTEN-selective sensitivity (Uterus d=-1.97, Ovary d=-1.68). Inavolisib shows inverse selectivity (PTEN-lost LESS sensitive). 49 non-PI3K combination candidates. PI3Kb-selective drugs not in PRISM.
- Phase 5: ~180K US PTEN-loss pts/yr. Priority: Breast > Melanoma > Lung. 14 cancer types with trial gaps. PIK3CA atlas cross-ref skipped (not yet available).
- Note: combination candidates mostly have BRD IDs without drug names (PRISM metadata limitation)
- Project status should advance from "development" to "analysis"
